overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, providing detailed specifications and an existing Statement of
  Work. The assistant first analyzed the codebase against these requirements,
  identifying several critical and medium-priority gaps. Subsequently, the
  assistant was tasked with implementing these missing features. Key
  implementations included adding a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness with
  critical safety warnings, integrating detection and tailored recommendations
  for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep
  Syndrome, and implementing a weighted scoring system for Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness. Furthermore, the assistant expanded the CSV data export to include
  all questionnaire responses, introduced new questions for pain severity and
  chronic fatigue screening with associated alerts, and added dedicated sections
  for medical and mental health history. This systematic approach ensured the
  application now aligns more closely with the original acceptance criteria,
  providing a more robust and informative patient questionnaire.
